WEBVTT

00:00.467 --> 00:01.733
<i> Previously on "Wrecked"...</i>
What is that?

00:01.735 --> 00:02.735
It's a priest character
from the game.

00:02.737 --> 00:04.202
I risked my life
to steal this.

00:04.204 --> 00:05.337
-What?!
-Come on!

00:05.339 --> 00:07.072
Hey, can you bark like a dog,
Half Pint?

00:07.074 --> 00:09.274
[ Yipping ]
[ Laughs ]

00:09.276 --> 00:10.609
Meat is murder.

00:10.611 --> 00:12.010
Oh, s-so you're
a hypocrite.

00:12.012 --> 00:14.412
I'm not a hypocrite.
I value all life.

00:14.414 --> 00:16.749
Does anyone know
any of our last names?

00:16.751 --> 00:19.417
See? We're no one
to each other.

00:19.419 --> 00:20.619
[ Electricity crackles ]

00:20.621 --> 00:21.820
[ Beeps, unlatches ]
She did it.

00:21.822 --> 00:23.488
Tell Declan
you found us all

00:23.490 --> 00:25.089
barricaded
at the power station!

00:25.091 --> 00:27.626
Once they get out of the
mansion, we can slip right in.

00:27.628 --> 00:28.893
[ Spits ]
Oh!

00:28.895 --> 00:29.828
I want them<i> dead.</i>

00:29.830 --> 00:31.496
Declan, what if they get
to the radio?

00:31.498 --> 00:33.265
That won't be a problem.

00:35.369 --> 00:39.972
♪♪

00:39.974 --> 00:42.641
I must say...

00:42.643 --> 00:44.977
you've put on
one hell of a show,

00:44.979 --> 00:48.046
but we now
have you surrounded,

00:48.048 --> 00:50.715
and you have
nowhere left to run.

00:50.717 --> 00:53.718
So I'll make this easy
for you.

00:53.720 --> 00:55.988
If you come out now,

00:55.990 --> 00:59.257
I will honor the terms
of our original agreement

00:59.259 --> 01:01.726
and spare
one of your lives.

01:01.728 --> 01:05.998
But if you decide
to stay inside my home,

01:06.000 --> 01:08.266
hiding like cowards,

01:08.268 --> 01:10.068
I will kill you all.

01:10.070 --> 01:12.604
♪♪

01:12.606 --> 01:14.673
As befitting a gentleman,

01:14.675 --> 01:16.341
I'll give you 30 seconds
to decide.

01:16.343 --> 01:17.676
Hey, Dec. Dec.
[ Grunts ]

01:17.678 --> 01:19.744
Your choice is --
What? What? What? What?!

01:19.746 --> 01:22.280
What are you
muttering about?!
I got-- I gotta go.

01:22.282 --> 01:23.816
You're pulling my leg.

01:23.818 --> 01:25.818
Can't that wait?
-No, it can't!

01:25.820 --> 01:28.620
Nature calls. I gotta answer
this sombitch.

01:28.622 --> 01:30.288
Honestly, I'd love
a little breather.

01:30.290 --> 01:32.891
My, uh, jumper's knee
is kinda acting up. I gotta --

01:32.893 --> 01:35.560
Hell, if we're taking a break,
I could slam a protein bar.

01:35.562 --> 01:37.295
Jesus Christ.

01:37.297 --> 01:38.831
Fi--
How long do you need?

01:38.833 --> 01:40.765
[ Sighs ]
Ideally, 15.

01:40.767 --> 01:43.235
But I mean, I could, like,
muscle it out in 10 if --

01:43.237 --> 01:45.237
Stop. Stop.
Stop talking.

01:45.972 --> 01:47.772
10 minutes!
You've got 10 minutes,

01:47.774 --> 01:50.509
then we come in
and kill you all, all right?!

01:50.511 --> 01:53.178
All right?!

01:53.180 --> 01:54.379
Christ on the cross.

01:54.381 --> 01:55.914
I'm trying to create
a sense of menace,

01:55.916 --> 01:57.982
a sense of -- of dread...
[ Farts ]

01:57.984 --> 01:59.651
...and you tits
are ruining it!

01:59.653 --> 02:01.520
[ Farting continues ]

02:01.522 --> 02:03.988
[ Wrapper crinkles ]

02:03.990 --> 02:05.758
Declan, you want
some of this, man?
Shut --

02:08.929 --> 02:16.601
♪♪

02:16.603 --> 02:19.804
Well, if we surrender,
maybe one of us could live?

02:19.806 --> 02:22.807
The rich --
they'll hunt whoever wins.

02:22.809 --> 02:26.478
Declan told me.
They're gonna kill us all.

02:26.480 --> 02:28.413
[ Thunder rumbles ]

02:28.415 --> 02:30.148
Well, then,
that's that.

02:30.150 --> 02:34.953
♪♪

02:34.955 --> 02:36.088
No.

02:36.090 --> 02:39.024
No, we are not
gonna die here today.

02:40.294 --> 02:43.361
We are gonna get out of this
together.

02:43.363 --> 02:44.863
Because Danny was right.

02:45.900 --> 02:47.099
We're a family.

02:47.101 --> 02:50.102
No, we're not.
You said it yourself.

02:50.104 --> 02:52.371
We don't even know
each other's last names.

02:52.373 --> 02:58.110
♪♪

02:58.112 --> 02:59.111
[ Sighs ]

02:59.113 --> 03:01.113
You want to know
what my last name is?

03:01.115 --> 03:03.515
♪♪

03:03.517 --> 03:06.050
It's the same
as all of yours.

03:06.052 --> 03:09.521
It's "Island."

03:09.523 --> 03:12.391
My name is Owen Island.

03:12.393 --> 03:14.259
♪♪

03:14.261 --> 03:16.328
-What?
-What are you talking about?

03:16.330 --> 03:18.597
-Your last name is "Island"?
-We--

03:18.599 --> 03:20.933
That's dumb.
I mean, is it Dutch?

03:20.935 --> 03:23.201
It's not [chuckles]
actually my last name.

03:23.203 --> 03:25.604
Obviously, I'm not Owen Isl--
I'm saying --

03:25.606 --> 03:27.539
I'm thinking of a name
that would unify us

03:27.541 --> 03:29.274
because we all crashed
on an island.

03:29.276 --> 03:30.542
Um...

03:30.544 --> 03:33.545
Look...

03:33.547 --> 03:36.548
when we crashed, we were
just a bunch of strangers

03:36.550 --> 03:38.817
stuck together.

03:38.819 --> 03:41.820
But we have been through
so much,

03:41.822 --> 03:44.356
that now we really are
like a family.

03:45.159 --> 03:48.160
So, it doesn't matter
what our last names were.

03:48.162 --> 03:51.964
What -- What -- What matters
is that now...

03:51.966 --> 03:54.833
we may as well share a name.

03:54.835 --> 03:57.770
My last name's Island,
too.

03:57.772 --> 03:59.437
I'm Danny Island.

03:59.439 --> 04:01.774
♪♪

04:01.776 --> 04:03.876
Then
I'm Florence Island.

04:05.646 --> 04:07.613
And I'm Jess Island.

04:10.250 --> 04:12.717
Yeah, I'm...

04:12.719 --> 04:14.252
Todd Island.

04:14.254 --> 04:17.922
But sometimes we bang, so...
are you, like, my sister?

04:17.924 --> 04:19.324
I don't really know
how this works.

04:19.326 --> 04:21.125
I'm Karen Cushman-Island.

04:21.127 --> 04:22.927
Didn't change my name
for Anthony,

04:22.929 --> 04:24.729
and I'm sure as shit
not gonna change it for you,

04:24.731 --> 04:26.865
but I'm happy
to hyphenate.

04:26.867 --> 04:28.200
All right, y'all ain't gonna
believe this,

04:28.202 --> 04:31.603
but my actual last name
<i> is</i> Island.

04:31.605 --> 04:33.672
I'm Bruce Island.
Hand to Jesus.

04:35.275 --> 04:36.741
I'm Stewart Island!

04:37.544 --> 04:40.278
Yep, I'm changing both my names.
I've always hated "Steve."

04:40.280 --> 04:42.748
Uh, Steve, that's not really
the --
Stewart.

04:43.684 --> 04:46.018
It's Stewart.
-[ Grunts ]

04:46.020 --> 04:47.419
Oh, my God!

04:47.421 --> 04:50.222
[ Groans ]

04:50.224 --> 04:52.090
And I'm Pack Island!

04:52.092 --> 04:55.227
Have you just been hiding there
this whole time?
Yeah, I have.

04:55.229 --> 04:56.761
And even though
it was kinda muffled,

04:56.763 --> 04:58.697
I agree with everything.

04:58.699 --> 05:01.033
And I'm done hiding.
I'm ready to fight!

05:01.035 --> 05:03.702
So let's stick it
to those rich assholes, huh?!

05:03.704 --> 05:05.037
Yeah!
-Yeah!

05:05.039 --> 05:06.705
-Yeah! Let's do it!
-I love family!

05:06.707 --> 05:09.574
So...what's the plan?

05:09.576 --> 05:13.045
♪♪

05:13.047 --> 05:16.248
Danny...
got any crazy ideas?

05:16.250 --> 05:20.452
♪♪

05:20.454 --> 05:22.187
Listen up, people!

05:22.189 --> 05:23.922
We've got
T-minus eight minutes

05:23.924 --> 05:26.525
to booby-trap the shit
out of this house.

05:26.527 --> 05:29.862
We're talking
homemade explosives...

05:29.864 --> 05:32.997
deadly kitchenware...

05:32.999 --> 05:35.534
marbles all over
the floor.

05:35.536 --> 05:39.672
They should be sliding
they asses all over this place.

05:39.674 --> 05:42.074
Oh, and, guys?

05:42.076 --> 05:44.008
Really think about
your last quip

05:44.010 --> 05:45.878
before you go in
for the kill.

05:45.880 --> 05:47.812
It should be
short and punchy,

05:47.814 --> 05:50.148
but also emotional.

05:50.150 --> 05:53.218
Like, for example,
I may say,

05:53.220 --> 05:55.354
"Well, isn't this rich?"

05:55.356 --> 05:56.821
Then bam!

05:56.823 --> 05:58.090
You see,
that played on

05:58.092 --> 05:59.892
both their financial
circumstances

05:59.894 --> 06:03.095
and my own
personal history.

06:03.097 --> 06:04.629
Actually...

06:04.631 --> 06:06.498
that one's really good.

06:06.500 --> 06:08.267
Shit. I may use that.

06:09.503 --> 06:11.503
Oh, wow.
You're done finally.

06:11.505 --> 06:14.306
Good. Have you, um...
eaten your snack?
Yeah.

06:14.308 --> 06:15.840
Taken your shit?
Oh, yeah.

06:15.842 --> 06:17.642
Knee feeling good?

06:17.644 --> 06:18.843
Yeah.

06:18.845 --> 06:20.845
Great. Well...

06:20.847 --> 06:23.582
let's hunt.

06:23.584 --> 06:25.517
All right.

06:25.519 --> 06:28.587
Time's up.

06:28.589 --> 06:30.455
Prepare to die.

06:30.457 --> 06:35.127
♪♪

06:37.664 --> 06:45.470
♪♪

06:45.472 --> 06:53.145
♪♪

06:53.147 --> 07:00.953
♪♪

07:00.955 --> 07:08.693
♪♪

07:08.695 --> 07:10.362
The vents?
[ Chuckles ]

07:10.364 --> 07:12.230
Too easy.

07:12.232 --> 07:14.299
Florence: Aah!

07:14.301 --> 07:16.635
[ Grunting ]

07:16.637 --> 07:19.304
-What the hell is this?!
-It's a red flag, mother--

07:19.306 --> 07:28.513
♪♪

07:28.515 --> 07:37.522
♪♪

07:37.524 --> 07:39.524
[ Exhales deeply ]

07:39.526 --> 07:42.126
♪♪

07:42.128 --> 07:43.896
[ Grunts ]

07:47.267 --> 07:48.867
The hell?

07:50.270 --> 07:51.603
Half Pint!

07:51.605 --> 07:53.205
Oh, shit.

07:53.207 --> 07:56.875
Looks like you got a little pair
of nuts on you after all.

07:56.877 --> 07:58.610
[ Gunfire ]
Aah!

07:58.612 --> 08:00.945
Well, where you going,
little doggy?

08:00.947 --> 08:02.547
I got a treat for you.

08:02.549 --> 08:11.423
♪♪

08:11.425 --> 08:20.298
♪♪

08:20.300 --> 08:22.034
[ Bruce coughing ]

08:23.770 --> 08:25.637
[ Breathing heavily ]

08:29.243 --> 08:31.510
Aah! Son of a --

08:31.512 --> 08:34.913
♪♪

08:34.915 --> 08:36.448
You sure
this is gonna work?

08:36.450 --> 08:38.917
Of course this is gonna work.
Why wouldn't it work?

08:38.919 --> 08:41.053
Because it's just
strings and marbles?

08:42.389 --> 08:44.657
Strings and marbles?

08:44.659 --> 08:47.926
You think this is just
strings and marbles?

08:49.463 --> 08:50.929
[ Chuckles ]

08:50.931 --> 08:53.866
Let me try and explain this
to you.

08:53.868 --> 08:56.134
Once he enters, he's gonna
slip on the marbles,

08:56.136 --> 08:58.002
stumble forward,
and trip the wire.

08:58.004 --> 09:01.005
That'll dump the syrup,
which will catch the fan,

09:01.007 --> 09:02.340
blasting him
with feathers.

09:02.342 --> 09:04.409
Momentarily blinded --
[ Groans ] --

09:04.411 --> 09:06.144
he'll reach for
the hot doorknob.

09:06.146 --> 09:09.347
[ Screams ]

09:09.349 --> 09:10.749
Then he'll fall
through the window.

09:10.751 --> 09:12.818
[ Screams ]
Plummeting!

09:13.888 --> 09:15.688
Straight to his death.

09:16.957 --> 09:18.690
Yeah, I just don't see
any of this actually working.

09:18.692 --> 09:20.559
[ Click in distance ]
[ Quietly ] Wait.
Shut the [bleep] up.

09:20.561 --> 09:22.761
Somebody's coming.

09:22.763 --> 09:24.429
This could be it.

09:24.431 --> 09:28.233
♪♪

09:28.235 --> 09:29.902
Hey! Get over here!

09:31.438 --> 09:32.704
Hey.

09:32.706 --> 09:34.172
It's the nerdy one.

09:34.174 --> 09:35.840
It would've been so much better
if it was Peabody,

09:35.842 --> 09:37.376
'cause we have that,
like, shared history --

09:37.378 --> 09:39.311
Danny!
[ Stammers ]

09:40.447 --> 09:42.380
[ Whispers indistinctly ]

09:42.382 --> 09:43.982
Shh! Shh, shh.

09:43.984 --> 09:45.384
[ Door opens ]

09:45.386 --> 09:48.120
Oh, I see.

09:48.923 --> 09:51.590
A little game of cat and --
Aah!

09:51.592 --> 09:52.391
[ Body thuds ]

09:52.393 --> 09:57.129
[ Marbles clattering ]

09:57.131 --> 09:58.397
Huh.

09:58.399 --> 10:01.000
You think he would've hit
the feathers by now.

10:03.203 --> 10:10.008
♪♪

10:10.010 --> 10:11.744
Oh.

10:16.082 --> 10:17.816
I did not
expect this.

10:17.818 --> 10:20.485
♪♪

10:20.487 --> 10:22.021
[ Lighter clinks ]

10:23.758 --> 10:26.291
Hey, there, friend.
Care for a drink?

10:26.293 --> 10:28.827
How about
our house specialty?

10:28.829 --> 10:32.697
We call it
a Molo-Todd cocktail.

10:32.699 --> 10:38.437
[ Screams ]

10:38.439 --> 10:40.406
[ Body thuds ]

10:42.643 --> 10:44.509
Hell, yeah!

10:44.511 --> 10:47.712
Are you freakin' kidding me?
Tell me someone saw that.

10:47.714 --> 10:49.247
Did anyone see that?

10:49.249 --> 10:52.450
Oh, my God!

10:52.452 --> 10:54.319
[ Grunting ]

10:54.321 --> 10:55.988
Freaking creep!

10:55.990 --> 10:59.057
Ow! That's me!
-Shit! Sorry.

10:59.059 --> 11:01.726
Aah!

11:01.728 --> 11:03.662
[ Both grunting ]

11:03.664 --> 11:10.402
♪♪

11:10.404 --> 11:11.403
Freeze!

11:11.405 --> 11:12.805
Drop the knife

11:12.807 --> 11:15.139
or I'll shoot you.
I swear to God.

11:15.141 --> 11:17.342
[ Breathing heavily ]

11:17.344 --> 11:19.478
You're the vegan,
right?

11:19.480 --> 11:20.745
What?

11:20.747 --> 11:22.080
What was it
you said again?

11:22.082 --> 11:24.949
That you respect
<i> all</i> life?

11:24.951 --> 11:27.686
[ Chuckles ]
You're not gonna kill me.

11:27.688 --> 11:32.891
♪♪

11:32.893 --> 11:34.827
Yeah, well...

11:34.829 --> 11:37.029
I'm a hypocrite, bitch.

11:37.764 --> 11:39.431
[ Gunshot ]

11:39.433 --> 11:40.733
[ Body thuds ]

11:42.569 --> 11:45.437
Ew!

11:45.439 --> 11:46.905
Eugh!

11:46.907 --> 11:49.107
[Bleep] It's in my mouth!

11:49.109 --> 11:51.710
Look at
his freakin' head.

11:51.712 --> 11:53.912
Oh, sick!

11:53.914 --> 11:56.081
Oh, it's so gross!

11:57.651 --> 11:59.184
Brewster: Half Pint!

11:59.186 --> 12:03.788
[ Breathing heavily ]

12:03.790 --> 12:06.124
Well, this is
more like it.

12:06.126 --> 12:10.663
Half Pint hiding
like a little bitch.

12:10.665 --> 12:12.731
I know you're in here.

12:14.201 --> 12:17.936
[ Singsong voice ]
Half Pint.

12:17.938 --> 12:20.105
[ Normal voice ]
Come on out, little doggy.

12:21.942 --> 12:24.476
Now, where could he be?

12:24.478 --> 12:25.677
[ Door open ]

12:25.679 --> 12:27.412
Aaaaaah!

12:27.414 --> 12:28.813
[ Grunting ]

12:28.815 --> 12:30.682
Take it! Take it!

12:30.684 --> 12:32.785
[ Both grunting ]

12:34.154 --> 12:36.020
Are you throwing
a trout at me?!

12:36.022 --> 12:41.894
♪♪

12:41.896 --> 12:47.966
♪♪

12:47.968 --> 12:50.969
[ Chuckles ]

12:52.172 --> 12:53.838
Well...
[ Gun cocks ]

12:53.840 --> 12:55.974
...looky here.

12:55.976 --> 12:59.644
Half Pint
is about to become No Pint.

12:59.646 --> 13:02.714
♪♪

13:02.716 --> 13:05.049
You know what?

13:05.051 --> 13:07.119
Do that little
funny dog bark

13:07.121 --> 13:09.154
for me one more time,
Half Pint.

13:10.524 --> 13:11.456
Hey.

13:11.458 --> 13:14.526
I said bark funny
like a dog.

13:14.528 --> 13:18.663
♪♪

13:18.665 --> 13:21.533
No.
I'm not a dog.

13:21.535 --> 13:24.536
I'm a medium-sized man.

13:25.606 --> 13:27.005
Suit yourself.

13:27.007 --> 13:28.307
Karen: Hey.

13:29.744 --> 13:30.943
Woof woof.

13:30.945 --> 13:32.344
[ Grunts ]

13:34.148 --> 13:35.814
That big, old bitch.

13:37.884 --> 13:39.551
[ Body thuds ]

13:39.553 --> 13:41.954
Oh, my God.

13:41.956 --> 13:43.956
Hell, yeah, Karen!

13:43.958 --> 13:46.625
And that line --
"Woof woof"?

13:46.627 --> 13:48.293
I mean, come on!

13:48.295 --> 13:50.094
That really
came full circle.

13:50.096 --> 13:52.831
I said it because that's
the sound a doggy makes.

13:54.835 --> 13:55.900
Yeah.

13:55.902 --> 14:03.108
♪♪

14:03.110 --> 14:05.710
[ Gunshots in the distance ]

14:05.712 --> 14:07.646
♪♪

14:07.648 --> 14:09.181
[ Gun cocks ]

14:09.183 --> 14:11.115
[ Breathing shakily ]

14:11.117 --> 14:13.385
Shit!

14:13.387 --> 14:15.920
Oh, yeah.

14:15.922 --> 14:18.323
[ Grunts ]

14:18.325 --> 14:23.796
♪♪

14:23.798 --> 14:29.668
♪♪

14:29.670 --> 14:31.135
[ Gun clicks ]

14:31.137 --> 14:33.005
Steve:
Well, well, well.

14:33.007 --> 14:36.809
Look at
these tables turning.

14:36.811 --> 14:40.279
♪♪

14:48.189 --> 14:51.857
♪♪

14:51.859 --> 14:54.526
[ Glass clinking ]
Shh, shh, shh.

14:54.528 --> 14:56.327
[ Whispering ]
Someone's inside.

14:56.329 --> 14:58.329
[ Whispering ]
Good thing we've got...

14:58.331 --> 14:59.631
my stick.

15:01.334 --> 15:03.535
Yeah.
No, totally.

15:03.537 --> 15:06.005
It's just...
I have a gun now.

15:06.007 --> 15:08.273
So maybe
we just use that.

15:08.275 --> 15:09.474
Yeah,
that makes sense.

15:09.476 --> 15:11.010
Let's do that.
Totally.

15:11.012 --> 15:12.211
Ready?

15:12.213 --> 15:16.215
♪♪

15:16.217 --> 15:18.684
[ Both breathing heavily ]

15:20.287 --> 15:22.221
[ Glass clinking ]

15:22.223 --> 15:24.689
Aaaaaaaaaaah!

15:24.691 --> 15:27.826
[ Slow-motion yelling,
glass breaking ]

15:27.828 --> 15:31.296
♪♪

15:31.298 --> 15:33.565
[ Breathing heavily ]
[ Gun clicking ]

15:37.504 --> 15:39.504
[ Muffled ]
What the [bleep]

15:39.506 --> 15:41.573
Oh, my God.
I am so sorry.

15:41.575 --> 15:43.308
I should've looked before
I started shooting.

15:43.310 --> 15:45.911
I realize that now.
This thing is<i> crazy!</i>

15:45.913 --> 15:47.046
Babe!

15:47.048 --> 15:48.847
[ Grunts ]

15:48.849 --> 15:51.182
[ Normal voice ] Ew. God.
You're covered in blood.

15:51.184 --> 15:53.051
Well, yeah.
Florence killed a guy.

15:53.053 --> 15:54.453
Oh, nice.

15:54.455 --> 15:57.589
I lit a dude on fire.
It was so dope.

15:57.591 --> 15:58.790
But it was also
pretty gnarly.

15:58.792 --> 16:01.260
I'm actually feeling
pretty weird about it.

16:01.262 --> 16:02.994
Where are the others?

16:02.996 --> 16:04.663
We're here.

16:04.665 --> 16:06.598
Oh, hey! What up?

16:06.600 --> 16:08.533
Did you guys
kill your guys, too?

16:08.535 --> 16:10.269
Big-time.
Karen crossbowed

16:10.271 --> 16:14.005
that John Wayne-looking dipshit
right in the chest!

16:14.007 --> 16:15.640
We used
marbles.

16:16.477 --> 16:19.544
Wait.
Where's Steve?
Declan: Right here.

16:19.546 --> 16:21.012
Nobody move

16:21.014 --> 16:24.816
or I will paint this room
with his brains.

16:24.818 --> 16:27.619
I'm sorry!
He got the jump on me.

16:27.621 --> 16:29.755
I was in the study, and
I took a gun off the wall,

16:29.757 --> 16:31.623
but it turned out to be more
of a decorative number.

16:31.625 --> 16:33.558
Quiet, please.
It wouldn't shoot.

16:33.560 --> 16:36.161
T-The barrel
wasn't even hollow.
Quiet!

16:36.163 --> 16:38.998
-The trigger was glued.
-Quiet. Don't -- Stop.

16:40.301 --> 16:41.833
Here's what's
going to happen.

16:41.835 --> 16:44.769
I'm going to my helicopter,
and I'm going to fly away.

16:44.771 --> 16:46.972
And if one of you so much
as farts in my direction,

16:46.974 --> 16:51.176
I will kill Steve,
and you<i> don't</i> want that, do you?

16:51.178 --> 16:54.045
Because
you're all family!

16:54.047 --> 16:57.349
Isn't that
your whole goddamn thing?!

16:58.719 --> 17:00.585
Let's go.
[ Gasps ]

17:00.587 --> 17:03.522
Jesus Christ,
your hands smell like piss.

17:03.524 --> 17:05.924
♪♪

17:05.926 --> 17:07.726
[ Door opens ]

17:07.728 --> 17:10.461
Hey, Declan.
Wait.

17:10.463 --> 17:12.131
We can figure
this out.

17:12.133 --> 17:13.732
No, we cannot.

17:13.734 --> 17:16.335
Because despite
your best efforts, you lost.

17:16.337 --> 17:18.069
It's like
I told Steve.

17:18.071 --> 17:19.738
If you want
to kill the king,

17:19.740 --> 17:23.274
you have to keep your eyes
on the prize.

17:24.011 --> 17:25.944
[ Quietly ]
Eyes on the prize.
So long, everyone.

17:25.946 --> 17:28.480
You know, I wish I could say
it's been a pleasure, but --

17:28.482 --> 17:30.415
but honestly it hasn't.

17:30.417 --> 17:32.617
I really despise
every one of you.

17:32.619 --> 17:34.153
[ Exhales sharply ]

17:34.155 --> 17:35.821
<i> Chestmate.</i>

17:37.358 --> 17:40.826
[ Breathing heavily ]
Did you just mean
to say "checkmate"?

17:40.828 --> 17:43.162
Oh, Christ. You are
the most stupid person --

17:43.164 --> 17:44.629
This is for Luther!

17:44.631 --> 17:46.231
Aah!
[ All screaming ]

17:46.233 --> 17:47.499
Aaaaaah!

17:47.501 --> 17:49.368
Ow! My eye!

17:49.370 --> 17:50.902
Oh!

17:50.904 --> 17:52.171
[ Grunts ]

17:52.173 --> 17:53.972
[ Body thuds ]

17:53.974 --> 18:00.045
♪♪

18:00.047 --> 18:02.381
I told you that little priest
would be the key

18:02.383 --> 18:03.915
to us getting
out of here.

18:03.917 --> 18:05.116
[ Laughs ]

18:05.118 --> 18:07.386
[ All cheering ]

18:07.388 --> 18:09.654
-Whoo!
-Hell, yeah!

18:09.656 --> 18:13.324
♪♪

18:13.326 --> 18:15.594
How the hell
do we get home?

18:15.596 --> 18:17.062
This is
a dumb question,

18:17.064 --> 18:19.264
but does anyone know
how to fly a helicopter?

18:19.266 --> 18:21.200
Bruce: Someone
say "helicopter"?

18:21.202 --> 18:22.401
[ Gasps ]

18:22.403 --> 18:25.871
-Bruce!
[ All cheering ]

18:25.873 --> 18:27.806
You know how
to fly a helicopter?

18:27.808 --> 18:31.342
Unless some other Bruce Island
did three tours in Desert Storm.

18:31.344 --> 18:33.412
Let's get the hell out of here
before I bleed out.

18:33.414 --> 18:36.281
Hell, yeah!
[ All cheering ]

18:36.283 --> 18:44.289
♪♪

18:44.291 --> 18:51.963
♪♪

18:51.965 --> 18:56.768
[ Helicopter blades
whirring slowly in distance ]

18:56.770 --> 19:00.239
[ Whirring quickens ]

19:00.241 --> 19:04.843
♪♪

19:04.845 --> 19:07.312
What's that sound?

19:07.314 --> 19:09.514
It's the chopper.

19:09.516 --> 19:10.982
Go!

19:10.984 --> 19:19.390
♪♪

19:19.392 --> 19:20.926
Aloha, babies.

19:20.928 --> 19:22.661
Danny: Chet,
what are you doing?!

19:22.663 --> 19:25.064
If I let you go back,
ol' Chester's toast.

19:25.066 --> 19:28.600
You'll throw me in
the clink just 'cause
I murdered some dudes.

19:28.602 --> 19:30.802
You still don't get it.

19:30.804 --> 19:33.472
Chet is a survivor,

19:33.474 --> 19:34.606
and I plan to --

19:34.608 --> 19:37.208
What?!

19:37.210 --> 19:38.410
What is
he saying?!

19:38.412 --> 19:40.211
I have
no idea!

19:40.213 --> 19:42.781
[ No audio ]

19:48.355 --> 19:50.355
Jess: He can't actually fly
that thing, can he?!

19:50.357 --> 19:53.024
Bruce: Without any training,
it's damn near impossible!

19:53.026 --> 19:57.829
[ All shouting indistinctly ]

19:57.831 --> 19:59.965
Oh, God bless.
He's gonna crash!

19:59.967 --> 20:01.032
Oh!

20:01.034 --> 20:08.707
♪♪

20:08.709 --> 20:12.044
[ Birds chirping ]

20:16.517 --> 20:18.617
[ Birds chirping ]

20:20.721 --> 20:23.254
Helen Mirren.

20:23.256 --> 20:25.324
Alive.

20:25.326 --> 20:27.526
James Earl Jones.
Ooh.

20:27.528 --> 20:29.728
I'm gonna say dead.

20:29.730 --> 20:32.598
I mean, can you even picture
a young James Earl Jones?

20:33.400 --> 20:35.768
Holy shit.
No, I can't.

20:36.737 --> 20:38.203
[ Chuckles ]

20:38.205 --> 20:39.938
Tom Cruise.

20:39.940 --> 20:41.740
Why would
Tom Cruise be dead?

20:41.742 --> 20:44.009
He does a lot
of his own stunts.

20:45.612 --> 20:47.146
[ Grunts ]

20:47.148 --> 20:48.947
[ Engine starts ]

20:50.217 --> 20:51.617
Michael Jackson.

20:52.886 --> 20:55.154
Michael Jackson died
like 10 years ago. What?

20:55.156 --> 20:56.688
What?

20:56.690 --> 20:58.157
Michael Jackson is dead?

20:58.159 --> 20:59.558
How do you
not know about this?

20:59.560 --> 21:02.227
Michael Jackson
the musician.

21:02.229 --> 21:03.228
Yeah.

21:03.230 --> 21:05.164
Oh, my God.

21:05.166 --> 21:07.366
That's so sad.

21:07.368 --> 21:09.100
Hold on a second.

21:09.102 --> 21:10.836
Mayday, mayday.
It's a distress call.

21:10.838 --> 21:11.970
Anybody out there?
Over.

21:11.972 --> 21:14.239
It was a huge deal.

21:14.241 --> 21:17.376
Well, at least the King of Pop
is moonwalking in Heaven.

21:17.378 --> 21:20.111
You know that people thought
he was a pedophile, right?

21:20.113 --> 21:21.380
What?!

21:21.382 --> 21:22.914
It is shocking to me

21:22.916 --> 21:24.516
that you don't know
about any of this.

21:24.518 --> 21:27.786
Mayday, mayday.
This is a distress call. Over.

21:29.923 --> 21:32.524
Nobody out there?
Thank you for nothing.
Talk to you never.

21:32.526 --> 21:35.126
Why aren't more people
talking about this?

21:35.128 --> 21:37.929
People were talking about this
10 years ago!

21:37.931 --> 21:40.265
Woman:<i> Hello?</i>

21:40.267 --> 21:42.734
<i> Hello?</i>

21:42.736 --> 21:44.203
<i> Are you there?</i>

21:44.205 --> 21:50.409
♪♪

21:50.411 --> 21:55.680
♪♪

21:55.682 --> 21:57.149
We're here.
